Home

About
About
Our Mission Statement
The Manatee River Fair Association, Inc.,
a private not-for-profit corporation, will seek to promote the agricultural and
economic strengths of Manatee County and to highlight Manatee County’s rich
heritage through the sponsorship of the annual Manatee County Fair and other
events throughout the year. The Manatee County Fair will provide a variety of
competition premium award programs, educational exhibits, arts and crafts,
entertainment, and organization displays in a family-friendly environment. The
operation of the Manatee County Fairgrounds throughout the year will further
support and enhance the Association’s promotion of local agriculture, commerce,
and history by providing financial support for the annual Manatee County Fair.
of
Transcript
The Manatee County Fair
The Manatee County fair is a wholesome community tradition. Packed with an endless variety of things to see, do and eat, the fair truly has something for everyone.
The eleven day Manatee County Fair is held each January at the
Manatee County Fairgrounds
in Palmetto, Florida.The City of Palmetto is located in Manatee County on the northern banks of the Manatee River and is approximately 40 miles south of Tampa, and 15 miles north of Sarasota with convenient access to Interstate 75 from S.R. 64 and S.R. 70 in Bradenton and Interstate 275 from U.S. 41 and U.S. 301 in Parrish.

Transcript
Youth Attractions
Annual Baby Pageant
Fair Queen Pageant
Annual Hay Bale Decorating Contest for 4-H and FFA Clubs
Annual Whip Popping Contest
4-H and FFA Livestock Judging
Creative Arts & Education
Arts and crafts submitted from members of the community representing all age groups. The culinary arts area displays the “best of the best,” recipes of Manatee County.
Exhibit Buildings
Manatee County businesses display their products, services and information.
Governmental offices/departments showcase their functions and provide information for the public from their booths.
Horticulture
The Master Gardeners Area offers the community a wealth of information about gardening through their special classes. Horticulture displays the best that’s homegrown.
Entertainment
The Main Stage brings local and national acts up close and personal.
Strolling Acts will perform throughout the grounds daily.
Fair Court Food
A smorgasbord of food featuring pizza, corn dogs, hot dogs, hamburgers, nachos, seafood, nuts, cinnamon rolls, cheesecake, fudge, funnel cakes, strawberry shortcake, elephant ears, cotton candy, candy apples, donuts and kettle corn to name just a few.
Food is provided throughout the Fair, with an oak covered picnic area for your enjoyment.
Expanded concessions near the Midway.
Diverse food selection
Livestock Arena - Sponsored By Mosaic
See Beef Breeding, Dairy, Dog, Goat, Horse, Heifer, Poultry, Rabbit, Steer and Swine Shows, as well as Steer and Swine Sales each Saturday.
Midway Rides & Amusements
All the exciting rides you can stand! -
Strates Shows
